# A selector chain (a."foo-bar".b) written across multiple lines, with
# the period at the end of each line. The renderer preserves authored
# line breaks: a segment whose Sel carries a Newline RelPos breaks onto
# its own indented line after the preceding period. Selectors never break
# on width, so a chain with no authored breaks (and no comments) stays
# flat - and a RelPos-stripped chain collapses (it has no layout intent).
#
# Trailing `//` comments on the segments (which the parser hangs at
# PosSuffix on each SelectorExpr, after its period) render in an aligned
# column via a docTable, matching | / & chains: the head segment's
# comment stays inline, continuation segments' comments column-align, and
# the field's own trailing comment (c3) is folded onto the last row so it
# aligns too. The comments force the multi-line table even without RelPos,
# since a `//` would otherwise swallow the following segment.
-- in.cue --
plain: a.
	"foo-bar".
	b
cmt: x. // c1
	"y". // c2
	z // c3
flat: a.b.c
-- out/relpos --
plain: a.
	"foo-bar".
	b
cmt: x. // c1
	"y". // c2
	z    // c3
flat: a.b.c
-- out/norelpos --
plain: a."foo-bar".b
cmt: x. // c1
	"y". // c2
	z    // c3
flat: a.b.c
